      • mxGetString

        int mxGetString​(MXArray pa,
                byte[] buf,
                com.sun.jna.NativeLong buflen)
        Converts a string array to a C-style string. The C-style string is in the local codepage encoding. If the conversion for the entire Unicode string cannot fit into the supplied character buffer, then the conversion includes the last whole codepoint that will fit into the buffer. The string is thus truncated at the greatest possible whole codepoint and does not split code- points.

      • mxGetUserBits

        Get 8 bits of user data stored in the mxArray header.

        NOTE: This state of these bits are not guaranteed to be preserved after API function calls.
